reviews.content:
There are four kinds of film adaptations from books;
Best: Fixes plot holes/ inconsistencies, bad pacing, etc. While keeping the wonder and spirit of the book. Chronicles of Narnia, Shadow and Bone, etc.Good film: Changed a lot of stuff, but was enjoyable as a seperate medium. Hamilton the musical
Good adaptation: Kept very close to the book, including it's flaws. The John Adams series.Bad: It's bad as a film and as an adaptation. Unfortunately, the much-anticipated Artemis Fowl movie, based on one of my favorite series of all times, joins other such infamous adaptations as Eragon and the Percy Jackson Movies.They completely changed the story and the characters, undercutting almost all the emotional and physical triumphs of the book series. They invalidated the characters. And, they tried to shoehorn in emotional moments, but cut out all the development so we went from point A1 to point Banana without any idea how we got there.I would give it one star, but the graphics were decent.I had thought there was so much potential for this movie, but none of it was realized. My family has agreed to never speak of it again, because it upsets us too much.
